This a Agenda created in Node.js The purpose is to let newbie people know about capabilities of the language. 
It includes files uploading and connection with MongoDB through the official driver. 
You will also see how to work with the express framework

The project was intented to set in a map the location of the contacts in your agenda 
by using the geolocator google API service. Even though is not implemented yet.

This project uses Twitter Bootstrap 2


INSTALLATION

Dependencies:

- Node.js
- Twitter Bootstrap
- MongoDB Driver
- Express Framework

To make this application to run just get the latest copy of the code into a folder then follow these steps:

1. cd application_folder
2. npm install
3. node app.js
4. From a browser look up for the url: http://localhost:3000
